<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBEFFE46DC2FCDBFC24A87B" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBEFFE46DC2FCDBFC24A87B" blockId="26.[178,1085,802,889]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">
Diagnosis: Distinguishable from superficially similar specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFBEFFE46E92FCDBFF67A87B" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pilosirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFBEFFE46E92FCDBFF67A87B" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">Pilosirus versus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a more obtuse pronotal tubercle (compare 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFBEFFE46E60FCFEFC33A87B" box="[784,934,867,889]" captionStart="Figs 133-144" captionStartId="40.[178,218,1358,1380]" captionTargetBox="[207,1052,231,1340]" captionTargetId="figure-1@40.[178,1084,212,1340]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figs 133-144: Aedeagi (133-140), Pronota (141-142), and Female mesodermal female reproductive organs (143-144). (133) Artoadenus similus phallus; (134) A. similus tegmen; (135) Tarandocerus auratus phallus; (136) T. auratus tegmen; (137) T. mexicanus phallus; (138) T. mexicanus tegmen; (139) T. testaceiceps phallus; (140) T. testaceiceps tegmen; (141) Pilosirus amazonicus; (142) P. versus; (143) Ambonoides retinoides female internal reproductive organs; (144) A. retinoides bursal plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294880/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">Figs. 141, 142</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBEFFE46DC2FC15FE94AF8B" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBEFFE46DC2FC15FE94AF8B" blockId="26.[178,1085,904,1161]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">
Description: Size: Length 7.0 mm; width 1.8 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFBEFFE46EE8FC15FC64A89C" box="[920,1009,904,926]" captionStart="Figs 157-160" captionStartId="51.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-59@51.[178,1085,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Figs 157-160: Habitus illustrations of (157) Isoforma planata, holotype; (158) I. plauta, holotype; (159) I. subgilva, holotype; (160) Pilosirus amazonicus, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282517/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">Fig. 160</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium mostly black, region behind eyes slightly flavotestaceous, gula flavotestaceous; pronotum mostly black, venter and upper sides flavotestaceous; mesoscutellum black; elytra black. Head: Antennal capitulum long (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFBEFFE46FF5FC7DFD45A8F4" box="[645,720,992,1014]" captionStart="Figs 70-80" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1351,1373]" captionTargetBox="[178,1100,235,1309]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1100,212,1333]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 70-80: Antennae. (70) Isoforma fritilla, female; (71) I. goryi, female; (72) Isoforma planata, female; (73) Pilosirus brunoi, male; (74) Isoforma subgilva, female; (75) Pilosirus amazonicus, female; (76) P. fasciatus, female; (77) Platynoptera carti, male; (78) P. flavohumeralis, male; (79) P. humeralis, male; (80) P. lyciformis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294864/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
), each capitular antennomere not as long as combined length of scape, pedicel, and funicle; antennal carina very prominent; EW/FW 10/15. Thorax: Pronotal anterior margin not projected at middle, side margin of disc with obtuse tubercle; PW/PL 43/43; elytral disc not strongly deflexed at sides, carina not present; EL/EW 145/35. Abdomen: Male pygidium not incised at distal margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBEFFE46DC2FB05FC9AAFAC" box="[178,783,1176,1198]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1539" type="distribution">
